sentences: Julian Michael Scanlan (born May 1, 1997), known professionally as Slushii, is an American musician, DJ, singer, songwriter, and record producer based in Los Angeles.
He began his musical career by joining psychedelic power-pop band Deuteronomy for three years until 2012, releasing one album, Propaganda.
He began his musical career by joining psychedelic power-pop band Deuteronomy for three years until 2012, releasing one album, Propaganda.
He became involved with dance music in 2013, using "DJ Swoon" as an alias.
He signed for Red Light Management in February 2016.
His first single for Canadian label Monstercat, Emptiness, was released on April 20, 2016.
He self-released his seven-track debut extended play titled "Brain Freeze" on May 20, 2016.
In March 2017, Slushii released a dubstep single titled "Catch Me".
On August 4, 2017, Slushii released his debut studio album titled Out of Light, which contained 13 songs, including "Dear Me".
